Dear all,

could you help in the following:

Several test are united in one test class. I want some initialization to be done ONCE for all tests.
I sow only 2 possibilities where to place initialization code:
1) setUp() method
2) constructor
But both are called n times, where n is number of testXXX() methods. For n=2 it looks like:
	constructor is called 
	constructor is called 
	.setUp is called 
	testOne is called 
	.setUp is called 
	testTwo is called

So, could you please advice how to achive one-time initialization.

// SAMPLE CODE THAT PRODUCES ABOVE OUTPUT
package itc_m.pass.test;

import junit.framework.*;

public class TestOfOneTimeInit extends TestCase {

public static Test suite() {
    return new TestSuite(TestOfOneTimeInit.class);
}

public TestOfOneTimeInit(){
  System.out.println(&quot;constructor is called&quot;);
}

protected void setUp(){
  System.out.println(&quot;setUp is called&quot;);
}

public void testOne(){
  System.out.println(&quot;testOne is called&quot;);
}

public void testTwo(){
  System.out.println(&quot;testTwo is called&quot;);
}

}


